      <h2 style="text-align: center;" class="font-weight-bold">Training Module 2: Assessment of Substance Use</h2>
      <hr>
      
      <p style="font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;">In the second module, you will learn how to assess substance use. You will learn to use single item drug use questions, conduct a functional analysis and substance use, and administer and interpret brief screening measures for assessing substances such as alcohol, marijuana, stimulants, and opioids. You will also consider effective screening of substance use in adolescent populations.</p>
      
      <p style="font-size:22px;font-weight:bold;">Learning Objectives</p>
      <div class="p-2">
        <p style="font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;">
          At the end of this program the learner will be able to:<br />
          1. Describe an approach to universal screening for substance use disorders.<br />
          2. Recognize the difference between low-risk, at-risk, and harmful patterns of substance misuse.<br />
          3. Identify common validated assessments to screen for unhealthy substance use. <br />
          4. Educate clients regarding alcohol portions that are equivalent to a standard drink unit.<br />
          5. Describe the diagnostic criteria for substance use disorders as defined by the DSM-V.<br />
          6. Recognize common assessment measures that can be used within treatment of substance use disorders. <br /> 
          7. Apply an approach to conducting a functional analysis of factors which contribute to substance misuse. <br />          
        </p>
      </div>

      {{> accreditation credits='3'}}      

      <p style="font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;">Please note that you will need to keep track of your progress. We advise you to write down your training module progress (e.g., video 2.3, 10:00 minutes) before you exit this screen. The webpage will not keep track of your progress for you.</p>				
